.SH NAME
if then else - conditional execution
.SH DESCRIPTION
Conditional execution; the syntax is the following :
.nf
if boolean then instructions,
elseif expri then instructions,
  ....
[else instructions],
end
.fi
.SH EXAMPLE
.nf
   i=2
   for j = 1:3, 
      if i == j then
        a(i,j) = 2; 
      elseif abs(i-j) == 1 then 
        a(i,j) = -1; 
      else a(i,j) = 0;
      end,
   end
.fi
